@NODE ACTIONS "Irritator - The Actions"

                                @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{U}The Actions@{UU}@{FG TEXT}

There are 13 different actions in Irritator so far, here is a description
of them all.

   @{B}Click LMB@{UB}    - Just clicks the left mouse button once.
   @{B}Click RMB@{UB}    - As above, but for the right mouse button.
   @{B}D-Click LMB@{UB}  - Double clicks the left mouse button.
   @{B}D-Click RMB@{UB}  - Double clicks the right mouse button ;).
   @{B}Hold LMB@{UB}     - Holds down the left mouse button for a random
                  time. Devastating in paint packages!
   @{B}Hold RMB@{UB}     - Holds down the right mouse button for a random
                  time. Even more devastating in paint packages!
   @{B}Flash Screen@{UB} - Flashes the current screen (uses DisplayBeep_).
   @{B}Requester@{UB}    - Puts up a User Error requester, using a text
                  from the Irritator.txts file.
   @{B}Belch@{UB}        - Makes the Amiga belch at you ;).
   @{B}Lines@{UB}        - Draws a random line on the current screen.
   @{B}Open CLI@{UB}     - Opens a new Shell window, and types in a command
                  taken from the Irritator.cmds file.
   @{B}FileReq@{UB}      - Opens an ASL file requester (see Note 1).
   @{B}TextType@{UB}     - Types a command into the current window (if it
                  accepts typing, like a Shell does) Also uses
                  Irritator.cmds to get its commands.

Note 1: The file requester is stubborn ;). If you click Cancel, it insists
you select a file. If you select a file, it insists that it doesn't exist
and goes away. ;)

